<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="021" project="code-quality-and-assurance-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Create Nightly Claude Code Review Prompt</title>
    <phase>3: Automation Pipelines</phase>
    <status>pending</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>020</dependencies>
    <blocks>043</blocks>
    <tags>automation, ai-review, prompt-engineering</tags>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Create the comprehensive review prompt file used by Claude Code in headless mode during the nightly
    quality workflow. Stored at scripts/quality/nightly-review-prompt.md. The prompt must instruct
    Claude to perform five review sections: (1) review recent changes from the last 24 hours using
    git log, (2) check pattern consistency across similar files, (3) sweep all 22+ ADRs for compliance,
    (4) flag TODO/FIXME items older than 30 days, (5) detect dead code. The prompt must specify a
    structured JSON output format so the nightly workflow can parse findings programmatically.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    AI prompt engineer specializing in code review automation and structured output design. Expert in
    crafting Claude Code headless prompts that produce consistent, parseable JSON results.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A production-ready prompt file at scripts/quality/nightly-review-prompt.md that, when executed by
    Claude Code in headless mode (`claude -p "$(cat scripts/quality/nightly-review-prompt.md)" --output-format json`),
    produces a structured JSON review containing findings from all five review sections. The JSON schema
    must be parseable by the nightly workflow's issue-update job.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      The nightly workflow (task 020) runs Claude Code headless mode with this prompt file as input.
      Claude Code will execute in the repository context with full file access. The prompt must be
      self-contained — it cannot rely on any runtime context injection other than the file system.

      The five review sections address different quality dimensions:
      1. Recent changes: Uses `git log --since="24 hours ago" --name-only` to scope review to what
         changed. Focuses on whether changes follow established patterns.
      2. Pattern consistency: Picks a random sample of similar files (e.g., 3 *Endpoints.cs files)
         and checks whether they follow the same structural patterns.
      3. ADR compliance: Sweeps the codebase for violations of all ADRs defined in .claude/adr/*.
         Focuses on high-signal ADRs: ADR-002, ADR-006, ADR-007, ADR-008, ADR-010, ADR-021, ADR-022.
      4. TODO/FIXME aging: Uses git log to find when each TODO/FIXME comment was introduced.
         Flag any item older than 30 days as requiring resolution.
      5. Dead code: Identifies unused using directives, private methods with no callers, unreachable
         code branches, commented-out code blocks > 10 lines.

      JSON output schema must include: summary (overall quality signal), findings array (each with
      section, severity, file, line, description, recommendation), metrics (count by severity), and
      a generated_at timestamp.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>scripts/quality/nightly-review-prompt.md (create)</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ (read — all ADR files to reference in the ADR compliance section)</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/code-review/references/review-checklist.md (read — existing review checklist to align with)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">The prompt must produce valid JSON output parseable by the nightly workflow. Define the JSON schema explicitly in the prompt so Claude follows it consistently.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">The prompt must be self-contained — all ADR references, checklists, and instructions must be embedded or referenced via relative file paths that exist in the repository.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">The prompt must instruct Claude to focus only on findings with actionable remediation — suppress informational observations that generate noise without driving action.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">Dead code detection must be scoped to src/ directory only. Do not flag dead code in tests/, projects/, or infrastructure/.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">TODO/FIXME aging requires git blame/log — the prompt must instruct Claude to use git commands to determine age, not just report existence.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-002.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-006.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-007.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-008.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-010.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-022.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/code-review/references/review-checklist.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read .claude/skills/code-review/references/review-checklist.md to understand the existing review checklist structure and align the nightly prompt with it (avoid duplication, complement it).</step>
    <step order="2">Read all ADR files in .claude/adr/ to compile the full list of ADRs (IDs and key constraints) that the ADR compliance section must check. Note the 22+ ADRs and identify the highest-signal ones for automated checking.</step>
    <step order="3">Design the JSON output schema: define the structure for summary, findings array (section, severity, file, line, description, recommendation), metrics object (critical_count, high_count, medium_count, low_count), and generated_at timestamp. Write this schema as a TypeScript interface in the prompt for unambiguous specification.</step>
    <step order="4">Write Section 1 of the prompt (Recent Changes Review): instruct Claude to run `git log --since="24 hours ago" --name-only --pretty=format:"%H %s"`, identify all changed files, and review each changed file for adherence to established patterns in surrounding similar files.</step>
    <step order="5">Write Section 2 of the prompt (Pattern Consistency): instruct Claude to sample three files of each significant type (*Endpoints.cs, *.tsx PCF controls, *Service.cs) and verify structural consistency — method ordering, comment style, error handling approach, import organization.</step>
    <step order="6">Write Section 3 of the prompt (ADR Compliance Sweep): for each of the seven high-signal ADRs, specify exactly what to search for (e.g., for ADR-010: count IService interfaces with single implementation; for ADR-006: check for legacy JS webresource patterns; for ADR-022: verify PCF files do not use React 18 createRoot).</step>
    <step order="7">Write Section 4 of the prompt (TODO/FIXME Aging): instruct Claude to find all TODO/FIXME comments in src/, use `git log -S "TODO" --diff-filter=A --follow -- {file}` to determine when each was introduced, and flag items where the introduction date is > 30 days ago.</step>
    <step order="8">Write Section 5 of the prompt (Dead Code Detection): instruct Claude to search for unused using directives in .cs files, private methods in classes where no other method or test references them, commented-out code blocks > 10 lines, and unreachable branches after return/throw statements.</step>
    <step order="9">Write the output instruction section: explicitly tell Claude to produce ONLY valid JSON matching the defined schema as its final output, with no prose before or after the JSON block. Include an example of a well-formed finding object.</step>
    <step order="10">Review the complete prompt for clarity, completeness, and testability. Ensure each section produces findings in the unified JSON schema. Verify the prompt would fit within Claude's context window for a typical repository state.</step>
    <step order="11">Write the complete prompt to scripts/quality/nightly-review-prompt.md.</step>
    <step order="12">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task 021 status from pending to completed.</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output type="file">scripts/quality/nightly-review-prompt.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>scripts/quality/nightly-review-prompt.md exists and contains all five review sections</criterion>
    <criterion>JSON output schema is explicitly defined in the prompt (TypeScript interface or equivalent)</criterion>
    <criterion>Section 1 (Recent Changes) uses git log --since="24 hours ago" to scope review</criterion>
    <criterion>Section 3 (ADR Compliance) covers at minimum ADR-002, ADR-006, ADR-007, ADR-008, ADR-010, ADR-021, ADR-022 with specific detection instructions for each</criterion>
    <criterion>Section 4 (TODO/FIXME Aging) instructs use of git commands to determine introduction date, not just report existence</criterion>
    <criterion>Section 5 (Dead Code) is scoped to src/ directory only</criterion>
    <criterion>Output instruction explicitly states: produce ONLY valid JSON, no prose before or after</criterion>
    <criterion>Each finding in the schema has: section, severity, file, line, description, recommendation</criterion>
    <criterion>An example finding object is included in the prompt to reduce output format drift</criterion>
    <criterion>TASK-INDEX.md updated to reflect task completion</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
